However, within the context of FOI Request No. LEX3172, this document, dated 1996, is described as detailing the "oldest advice" provided by the Australian Bureau of Statistics (ABS) to the Australian Electoral Commission (AEC) concerning membership testing methodology. This document is directly relevant to FOI Request No. LEX3172 as it pertains to the "earliest advice" sought regarding ABS recommendations to the AEC on membership testing methodology. While the specific content is not present, its described nature aligns with the request for documents from 1996 demonstrating the ABS's role in shaping the AEC's policy. The FOI request overview also clarifies that while documents relating to "earliest advice" were provided, no documents pertaining to the "most recent advice" were released.
